same issues as above - different HP model = EliteBook 8460p with WIN pro64 <span style="color:#323d4f;"><span style="font-family:Lucida Grande, Trebuchet MS, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#ececec;">Creators </span></span></span>ver 1703 - tried above driver downloaded solution and quite a lot of others even from suggestion on the following page (might work for somebody else ) :<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://temposemi.com/applications/windows-10-driver-support-2/">https://temposemi.com/applications/wind ... support-2/</a><!-- m --><br />as it looks like they (<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://temposemi.com">http://temposemi.com</a><!-- m -->) have bought/inherited this part of IDT drivers and are suggesting the following 2 sources<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.catalog.update.microsoft.com/Search.aspx?q=IDT">https://www.catalog.update.microsoft.co ... aspx?q=IDT</a><!-- m --><br />plus<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.catalog.update.microsoft.com/Search.aspx?q=">https://www.catalog.update.microsoft.com/Search.aspx?q=</a><!-- m -->&quot;Tempo&quot;%20%2B%20&quot;Audio&quot;<br />NONE worked <br />Solution for Classic Shell to continue working &quot;normally&quot; was to reinstall as administrator AND in compatibility mode the old WIN64bit 8.1 drivers (ver 6.10.6433.0) from :<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://support.hp.com/us-en/drivers/selfservice/closure/hp-elitebook-8460p-notebook-pc/5056942">https://support.hp.com/us-en/drivers/se ... pc/5056942</a><!-- m --><br />Hope that this will save a few wasted hours to somebody out there <br />THANK YOU Ivo.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=19578">abs</a> — Sun Apr 30, 2017 5:09 am</p><hr />
