<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7502&amp;p=32277#p32277"><![CDATA[
Problem resolved.<br />Searched HP support site and found an update to Beats Audio<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/Notebook-Audio/Beats-Audio-Control-Panel/m-p/6077387#M83314">http://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/Notebook-A ... 387#M83314</a><!-- m --><br />This is a download for sp63555.exe. With it installed, Beats Audio functions, the red beats light and mute button hardware, Beats Audio in Control Panel, and last ..  Classic Shell v4.3.0.!! <br /><br />I hope this can help someone with the same problem. Thanks for supporting this forum.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=19257">MerleNicholson</a> — Tue Apr 18, 2017 2:26 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
